1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with community detection in social tagging systems, which is a subfield of social network analysis. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a tensor decomposition approach for learning mixed membership community models, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - Although not directly related to software engineering, the paper may be relevant to software developers who are interested in building social tagging systems. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may be of interest to researchers working on algorithms for community detection in hypergraphs. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper may be relevant to researchers working on information retrieval systems that use social tagging data.
